Daily Life:\n\n\ud83d\udcabSet Boundaries- Protect your time and energy like the precious resources they are.\n\ud83d\udcabRest Well- Prioritize sleep and downtime instead of running on empty.\n\ud83d\udcabPractice Moderation- Enjoy what you love whether that's food, socializing, or Netflix without overindulging.\n\ud83d\udcabMindful Consumption- Notice what you\u2019re taking in (media, conversations, food) and ask: Is this nourishing me?\n\ud83d\udcabChannel Your Energy Wisely- Put your focus into what truly matters to you, not into endless scrolling or stress.\n\nWhen we \ud83c\udf3f\n\nIn yoga, Satya means truthfulness. It encourages us to be honest in our words, actions, thoughts, and with ourselves. It\u2019s about living in alignment with your deepest values, not just avoiding lies. \n\nPracticing Satya in daily life can look like:\n\nSaying what you actually feel (with kindness and empathy)\nHonoring your limits instead of pushing past them\nLetting go of what \u201cshould be\u201d and accepting what is\n\nWhen we are practicing Satya we should be asking ourselves questions like, \u201cAm I being true to myself right now?\u201d \ud83d\ude4f \"Am I saying something about someone else without knowing the entire story?\" \ud83d\ude4f \"Am I leaving something out of my narrative (omission) to avoid a potential consequence?\" \ud83d\ude4f\n\nWhen we pause, ask, and listen, we create space for more authenticity, peace, and connection.
